'''Inés Temple Arciniaga''' is a Peruvian businesswoman. She is president of Lee Hecht Harrison Peru and Lee Hecht Harrison Chile.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=September 2012|title=Education: The Battle for Talent|url=http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=f5h&AN=82361926&site=ehost-live|journal=Latin Trade (English)|volume=20|issue=5|page=88|doi=|pmid=|access-date=6 July 2016|subscription=yes|via=EBSCO}}</ref>

Temple has a [[Bachelor of science|BS]] in [[business administration]] from [[New York University]] in [[New York City]], and an [[MBA]] from the [[Adolfo Ibañez School of Management]] in [[Miami, Florida]].{{cn|date=November 2018}} She has 3 children.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://larepublica.pe/18-11-2007/senora-ejecutiva|title=Señora Ejecutiva|last=Arriola|first=Luis|date=18 November 2007|work=La Republica|language=Spanish|access-date=6 July 2016|via=}}</ref>

She set up the Peruvian branch of Drake Beam Morin, a [[human resources]] company, in 1993. In 2011, Drake Beam Morin was acquired by [[Adecco]] and merged with its existing [[Lee Hecht Harrison]] subsidiary.<ref name=adecco>[https://press.adeccogroup.com/news/adecco-completes-the-acquisition-of-drake-beam-morin-inc-dd37-2cb12.html Adecco completes the acquisition of Drake Beam Morin, Inc.] (press release). Adecco Group. Accessed November 2018.</ref>

She wrote ''Usted S.A - Empleabilidad & Marketing Personal''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbesagencycouncil/2016/04/19/how-to-master-your-personal-brand-by-thinking-like-a-ceo/#42c7d7726458|title=How To Master Your Personal Brand By Thinking Like A CEO|last=Davis|first=Raoul|date=19 April 2016|work=Forbes|access-date=6 July 2016|via=}}</ref> in 2010; it has gone through several editions and was among the top selling books in Perú for 2013.<ref name="test2">[http://www.peruthisweek.com/news-here-are-2013s-10-best-selling-books-for-peru-101756 Peru This Week's 2013's Best Selling Books for Peru]</ref>

She has chaired the [[board of directors]] of Perú2021,<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170123035622/http://empresa.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1054&Itemid=358|title=Agenda|last=|first=|date=6 March 2014|work=Forum Empresa|language=Spanish|access-date=6 July 2016|via=}} Archived 30 December 2017.</ref> and of [[CARE Peru]].{{cn|date=November 2018}}

