{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name = José Jaikel | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = José Antonio Jaikel Aguilar | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1966|4|3}} | birth_place = [[Alajuela]], [[Costa Rica]] | height = {{convert|1.80|m|ftin|abbr=on}} | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1986–1993 |clubs1 = [[Deportivo Saprissa|Saprissa]] |caps1 = |goals1 = | years2 = 1994 |clubs2 = [[C.S. Herediano|Herediano]] |caps2 = |goals2 = | nationalyears1 = 1990–1994 | nationalteam1 = [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] | nationalcaps1 = 5 | nationalgoals1 = 2 }}
{{spanish name 2|Jaikel|Aguilar}} '''José Antonio Jaikel Aguilar''' (born 3 April 1966 in [[Alajuela]]) is a former [[Costa Rica]]n [[association football|football]] player who played most of his career with [[Deportivo Saprissa]], during the 1980s and 1990s.
==Club career== Nicknamed ''El Tanque'', because of his strength and build, the [[striker (football)|striker]] won several national championships with Saprissa, as well as one [[CONCACAF Champions Cup]]s. He also played with [[C.S. Herediano|Herediano]], before retiring at only 28 years of age.<ref name=Prensa/>
==International career== He was part of the [[Costa Rica national football team|national team]] squad, that played in the [[1990 FIFA World Cup]]<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/worldcup/italy1990/teams/team=43901/index.html Costa Rica squad list] - FIFA</ref> held in [[Italy]], but didn't have any actual playing time.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]] |title=World Cup 1990 finals |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tables/90full.html |accessdate=2009-08-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110511104746/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/90full.html |archivedate=11 May 2011 |df= }}</ref>
His final international was a January 1994 [[friendly match]] against [[Norway national football team|Norway]].
