{{Infobox Mayor |name = Nicolae Bivol |image = |caption = |office = Member of the [[Sfatul Ţării|Moldovan Parliament]] |term_start = 1917 |term_end = 1918 |predecessor = |successor = |office2 = [[Mayor of Chişinău]] |term_start2 = 1923 |term_end2 = 1924 |predecessor2 = [[Gherman Pântea]] |successor2 = [[Vasile Bârcă]] |term_start3 = 1925 |term_end3 = 1926 |predecessor3 = [[Vasile Bârcă]] |successor3 = [[Sebastian Teodorescu]] |birth_date = {{Birth date|1882|06|01}} |birth_place = [[Ialoveni]] |death_date = {{Death date and age|1940|07|03|1882|06|01}} |death_place = [[Chişinău]] |resting_place = |resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|display=inline,title}} --> |nationality = |party = [[National Liberal Party (Romania, 1875)|National Liberal Party]] |spouse = |relations = Petru Bivol (father) |children = |residence = |alma_mater = [[University of Dorpat]] |occupation = |profession = |religion = [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Eastern Orthodoxy]] |signature = |website = |footnotes = }} '''Nicolae Bivol''' (June 1, 1882 in [[Ialoveni]] – July 3, 1940 in [[Chişinău]]) was a [[Bessarabia]]n politician, member of the [[Sfatul Ţării]] between 1917–1918, and [[Mayor of Chişinău]] in two terms between 1923-1924 and 1925-1926.<ref>{{cite web |author=VIP Magazin |url=http://www.vipmagazin.md/tema/10_plus_3_primari_ai_Chi%C5%9Fin%C4%83ului/ |title=10+3 primari ai Chişinăului |publisher=VIP Magazin |date=October 2010 |accessdate=2014-05-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202222642/http://www.vipmagazin.md/tema/10_plus_3_primari_ai_Chi%C5%9Fin%C4%83ului/ |archivedate=2013-12-02 |df= }}</ref>
== Biography ==
In 1902, Nicolae Bivol graduated from [[Chişinău Theological Seminary]], where one of his classmates was [[Teodor Neaga]]. Then he studied at [[University of Dorpat]]. Nicolae Bivol was a businessman and served as [[mayor of Chişinău]]. In 1935, Bivol edited [[Viaţa Noastră]] in [[Chişinău]].
